cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "chimerax-vampnet: VAMPnet + MSM analysis of protein conformational landscapes in UCSF ChimeraX"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata in this file."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Hough
    given-names: Morgan
    email: morgan.hough@gmail.com
abstract: >
  A UCSF ChimeraX bundle that brings VAMPnets (Mardt et al. 2018) and
  Markov state modeling to protein conformational ensemble analysis.
  Loads heterogeneous ensembles (MD, AlphaFlow, BioEmu, Boltz-2,
  MarS-FM) on equal footing, fits a VAMPnet via deeptime, and surfaces
  metastable states + transition rates as ChimeraX models, animations,
  and structured CLI output. Every command returns JSON-serializable
  data so an MCP-capable LLM agent (Claude Desktop, Cursor, Continue)
  can drive an adaptive analysis loop via the included HTTP bridge.
license: MIT
